For Windows:
1. Open command promp or terminal in VS Code
2. If python is not installed type: 
   go to this website to download python: https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
   Then run the installer

For Linux(Ubuntu):
1. Open terminal
2. If python is not installed type: sudo apt update
   then press enter
   then type: sudo apt install python3
   then press enter

For both Windows and Linux:
After you installed python you need to install these libraries, copy the text below and paste in on command promp(Windows), terminal(Linux) then press enter:
pip install matplotlib
pip install pandas
pip install numpy
pip install scipy
pip install scikit-learn
pip install snapml
